The paper discusses workload characterization and performance analysis of high performance computing (HPC) systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses resource utilization and performance optimization, which could fall under Performance (cs.PF) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) categories. The paper also analyzes the types of parallelism employed by users, which could fall under Computer Engineering (cs.CE) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories.
